truefeedback.text:
{@if node3_test=1 then "<br>" else ""@}

<p>The domain you have given is missing values of \(x\) for which we can evaluate \(f\).
<br>For example, \({@if ta1<ans1 then ta1 else ta2@} \notin \{ x \in \mathbb{R} : {@ans1@} \leq x \leq {@ans2@}\}\). However,</p>

<p style="margin-left: 30px">\(\begin{align*}
f({@if ta1<ans1 then ta1 else ta2@}) &= \sqrt{{@bb^2@} - {@if ta1<ans1 then ta1^2 else ta2^2@}} \\
&= \sqrt{{@if ta1<ans1 then bb^2-ta1^2 else bb^2-ta2^2@}} \\
&= {@if ta1<ans1 then sqrt(bb^2-ta1^2) else (bb^2-ta2^2)@}
\end{align*}\)</p>

<p>Therefore \({@if ta1<ans1 then ta1 else ta2@} \in Dom(f)\).</p>

